      • addCalcdProducts

        public static void addCalcdProducts(String molStr,
                                    int rxnId,
                                    String[] calcdProdStrs)
                             throws DBException
        Stores the products, calculated by Reactor, of a particular set of reaction conditions operating on a particular molecule or group of molecules. Called from SynthSolver.

        According to this and this discussion, we need to get a ConnectionHandler that uses the inner OracleConnection of the pooled connection, but later we need to close the outer pooled connection without closing the inner one.

        Note: Synchronization of this method requires any call to this method to be complete before another call to this method can be executed.

        Parameters:
        molStr - starting material(s) of the reaction
        rxnId - the ID number of the reaction conditions operating on the molecule or group of molecules
        calcdProdStrs - the products calculated by Reactor, as an array of strings; normally a single string that contains all the products fused, but can contain multiple strings for products that have properties that need to be preserved
        Throws:
        DBException - if there's a problem writing to the database

        Parameters:

        rxnId - the ID number of the reaction conditions operating on the molecule or group of molecules
        calcdProdStrs - the products calculated by Reactor, as strings
        Throws:
        DBException - if there's a problem writing to the database

                                 throws DBException

      • getConHandler

        private static ConnectionHandler getConHandler(Connection con)
                                        throws SQLException
        Gets a connection handler for updating the JChem table. Called only from addCalcdProducts() because that's where we write a CLOB to the JChem table. See the discussions here and here for why it's necessary to get the inner OracleConnection to write a CLOB.
        Parameters:
        con - a pool connection
        Returns:
        a connection handler activated with an inner OracleConnection, or null if it can't get the inner OracleConnection
        Throws:
        SQLException - if can't get a pool connection
